# MyChair - Master Engineering Rules

# 1. Project Overview

Project:
MyChair - Multi Tenant Salon ERP SaaS

Purpose:
Enterprise-grade salon management platform supporting:

* multi-tenant salons
* employee management
* appointments
* services
* billing
* analytics
* onboarding
* notifications

Architecture Goals:

* scalable
* reusable
* maintainable
* production-ready
* modular
* tenant-isolated
* RBAC protected

---

# 2. Frontend Rules

Frontend Stack:

* React
* TypeScript
* Tailwind CSS
* Redux Toolkit
* RTK Query
* Formik

Frontend Architecture:

* Keep existing pages-based architecture
* Reuse current project structure
* Do not migrate architecture unless explicitly requested

Current Structure:
src/

* assets/
* components/
* constants/
* context/
* hooks/
* pages/
* redux/
* routes/
* utils/

---

# 3. Common Component Rules

IMPORTANT:
Before creating any UI component:

1. Check components/common first
2. Reuse existing common component
3. Extend existing reusable component if needed
4. Create new component only if reusable version does not exist

Never duplicate:

* tables
* buttons
* modals
* dropdowns
* search bars
* loaders
* tooltips
* chips
* pagination
* cards
* toaster logic

Common Components Location:
src/components/common/

Mandatory Shared Components:

* CommonTable
* CommonPagination
* CommonModal
* CommonButton
* CommonDropdown
* CommonSearch
* CommonLoader
* CommonTooltip
* CommonStatusChip
* CommonCard
* CommonToaster

---

