* responsive design

---

# 8. Backend Rules

Backend Stack:

* FastAPI
* MongoDB
* Beanie ODM
* JWT Authentication
* REST APIs

Architecture:

* Modular Monolith
* Service Layer Architecture
* RBAC authorization
* Tenant isolation

Backend Standards:

* keep routes/controllers thin
* business logic inside services
* reusable utilities
* centralized exception handling
* reusable validators
* scalable architecture

---

# 9. Multi-Tenant Rules

Every salon is a tenant.

Tenant Rules:

* every business entity must contain tenant_id
* APIs must automatically filter by tenant_id
* cross-tenant access prohibited
* super_admin bypasses tenant filtering
* super_admin tenant_id must be null

Tenant Scoped Entities:

* users
* employees
* services
* appointments
* clients
* inventory
* notifications
* subscriptions
* analytics

---

# 10. RBAC Rules

Roles:

* super_admin
* salon_owner
* salon_manager
* salon_admin
* employee

Authorization Rules:

* RBAC enforced at API and service layer
* users cannot manage higher roles
* users cannot access outside tenant
* unauthorized access must return proper errors

---

# 11. Authentication Rules

Authentication:

* JWT access token
* refresh token
* bcrypt password hashing
* multi-session support

Password Rules:

* minimum 8 characters
* uppercase
* lowercase
* number
* special character

Security:

* never store raw passwords
* never expose password hashes

---

# 12. API Rules

API Versioning:
Use:
/api/v1/

All APIs must support:

* pagination
* filtering
* sorting
* searching
* validation
* error handling

Standard API Response:
{
"success": true,
"data": {},
"message": "",
"error": null
}

---

# 13. Database Rules

Database:

* MongoDB
* Beanie ODM

All entities should include:

* id
* tenant_id
* created_at
* updated_at
* created_by
* updated_by
* is_deleted
* deleted_at

Soft Delete Rules:
Use soft delete for:

* users
* salons
* services
* appointments
* employees
* clients

Never permanently delete production data.

---

# 14. Audit Logging Rules

Track:

* login activity
* role changes
* appointment changes
* invitation actions
* billing changes
* employee changes

Audit Log Fields:

* actor_id
* tenant_id
* entity_type
* entity_id
* old_value
* new_value
* timestamp
* action_type

Audit logs:

* immutable
* never editable
* never deletable

---

# 15. Invitation Rules

Invitation Flow:

1. invitation created
2. email sent
3. invitation accepted
4. password setup
5. onboarding completed

Invitation Rules:

* secure signed tokens
* expires after 7 days
* single-use token
* resend invalidates old token

---

# 16. Appointment Rules

Validate before booking:

* employee availability
* leave conflicts
* overlapping appointments
* valid time slot
* service availability

Appointment Statuses:

* pending
* confirmed
* in_progress
* completed
* cancelled
* no_show
* rescheduled

Prevent double booking.

---

# 17. Notification Rules

Supported Channels:

* email
* in-app
* websocket realtime

Provider:

* Resend

Track:

* delivery status
* provider response
* failure reason

---

# 18. Security Rules

Use:

* JWT auth
* HTTPS
* CORS protection
* rate limiting
* input validation
* RBAC authorization
* tenant validation

Store secrets in environment variables only.

---

# 19. Performance Rules

Use Redis caching for:

* sessions
* tenant configs
* appointment slots
* employee availability

Performance Standards:

* pagination for large datasets
* optimized queries
* async email sending
* async notification processing

---

# 20. Timezone Rules

* database stores UTC only
* backend returns UTC
* frontend handles timezone conversion
* all calculations use UTC internally

---

# 21. Future Scalability Rules

Architecture must support:

* WhatsApp integrations
* payment gateways
* Google calendar
* Outlook calendar
* analytics
* PWA
* mobile apps
* AI features
* queue systems
* microservice extraction

---

# 22. AI Generation Rules

Before generating code:

1. check existing architecture
2. reuse existing components
3. reuse existing services/hooks/utils
4. avoid duplicate logic
5. keep code modular
6. maintain UI consistency
7. maintain RBAC rules
8. maintain tenant isolation

When creating new UI:

* always use common components
* always reuse existing tables/modals/buttons
* create reusable versions only if needed

When creating APIs:

* always validate tenant access
* always validate RBAC
* always use pagination/filter/search
* always return standard response format

Code generated must always be:

* production-ready
* scalable
* reusable
* maintainable
* ERP-ready
